{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871569965,"sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31a83c001op4yFeTBXOtldb","messageID":"msg_d7a318d630013FzasnKSQR70cO","sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8ececcd4331241abad30b13756778c58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n14: - **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n15: - **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### System Context\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         User CLI                                 │\n26: │  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent --provider k8s            │\n27: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n28:                               │\n29:                               ▼\n30: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n31: │                     CLI Layer (main.py)                          │\n32: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n33: │  │ Typer app.publish()                                       │   │\n34: │  │  - Parse CLI options                                      │   │\n35: │  │  - Create PublishRuntime                                  │   │\n36: │  │  - Handle errors (_handle_error)                          │   │\n37: │  │  - Display Rich Progress spinner                          │   │\n38: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                               │\n41:                               ▼\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                    Runtime Layer                                 │\n44: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n45: │  │ PublishRuntime.publish()                                  │   │\n46: │  │  1. Load metadata (MetadataService)                       │   │\n47: │  │  2. Apply option overrides                                │   │\n48: │  │  3. Prepare image (_prepare_image_for_publishing)         │   │\n49: │  │  4. Deploy via provider                                   │   │\n50: │  │  5. Update metadata                                       │   │\n51: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n52: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53:                               │\n54:               ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n55:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n56: ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐\n57: │ AgentCube       │ │ Kubernetes      │ │ Docker          │\n58: │ Provider        │ │ Provider        │ │ Service         │\n59: │ (CR API)        │ │ (Deployment)    │ │ (Push)          │\n60: └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n61:               │               │               │\n62:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n63: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n64: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                            │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐     │\n66: │  │ AgentRuntime CR  │  │ Deployment + NodePort Service    │     │\n67: │  │ (agentcube)      │  │ (k8s)                            │     │\n68: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────┘     │\n69: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Component Diagram\n73: \n74: ```\n75: PublishRuntime\n76: ├── MetadataService (load/save metadata)\n77: ├── DockerService (push_image, login, tag)\n78: ├── Provider Selection\n79: │   ├── AgentCubeProvider (provider=\"agentcube\")\n80: │   │   ├── CustomObjectsApi (CR create/patch)\n81: │   │   ├── CoreV1Api (namespace)\n82: │   │   └── _sanitize_name()\n83: │   │   └── _ensure_namespace()\n84: │   └── KubernetesProvider (provider=\"k8s\")\n85: │       ├── AppsV1Api (Deployment)\n86: │       ├── CoreV1Api (Service, Namespace)\n87: │       ├── _create_deployment()\n88: │       ├── _create_service()\n89: │       ├── wait_for_deployment_ready()\n90: │       └── _sanitize_name()\n91: └── _update_publish_metadata()\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Data Structures\n97: \n98: ### AgentMetadata Extensions (Pydantic BaseModel)\n99: \n100: ```python\n101: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n102:     agent_name: str\n103:     description: Optional[str] = None\n104:     language: str = \"python\"\n105:     entrypoint: str\n106:     port: int = 8080\n107:     build_mode: str = \"local\"\n108:     region: Optional[str] = None\n109:     version: Optional[str] = None\n110:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n111:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n112:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n113:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n114:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n115:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n116:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n117:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n118:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n119:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n120:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n121:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None       # NEW: Assigned by AgentCube\n122:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n123:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # NEW: Deployment info\n124: \n125:     @validator(\"language\")\n126:     def validate_language(cls, v):\n127:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n128:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n129:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n130:         return v.lower()\n131: \n132:     @validator(\"build_mode\")\n133:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n134:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n135:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n136:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n137:         return v.lower()\n138: \n139:     @validator(\"port\")\n140:     def validate_port(cls, v):\n141:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n142:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n143:         return v\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### k8s_deployment Field Structure\n147: \n148: ```python\n149: k8s_deployment: Dict[str, Any] = {\n150:     \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\" | \"Deployment\",\n151:     \"deployment_name\": str,\n152:     \"service_name\": str,           # k8s provider only\n153:     \"namespace\": str,\n154:     \"replicas\": int,\n155:     \"node_port\": int,              # k8s provider only\n156:     \"service_url\": str,            # k8s provider only: \"http://localhost:{node_port}\"\n157:     \"agent_id\": str,               # agentcube provider only\n158:     \"status\": \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"error\",\n159:     \"error\": Optional[str],        # Set on failure\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### PublishOptions (Internal)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: @dataclass\n167: class PublishOptions:\n168:     workspace: Path\n169:     version: Optional[str] = None\n170:     image_url: Optional[str] = None\n171:     image_username: Optional[str] = None\n172:     image_password: Optional[str] = None\n173:     description: Optional[str] = None\n174:     region: Optional[str] = None\n175:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n176:     provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n177:     node_port: Optional[int] = None\n178:     replicas: Optional[int] = None\n179:     namespace: Optional[str] = None\n180:     verbose: bool = False\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### Typer Command Interface\n188: \n189: ```python\n190: @app.command()\n191: def publish(\n192:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", \n193:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n194:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\",\n195:         help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n196:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\",\n197:         help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n198:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\",\n199:         help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n200:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\",\n201:         help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n202:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\",\n203:         help=\"Agent description\"),\n204:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\",\n205:         help=\"Deployment region\"),\n206:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n207:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n208:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n209:         help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n210:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\",\n211:         help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n212:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\",\n213:         help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n214:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\",\n215:         help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n216:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\",\n217:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n218: ) -> None:\n219:     \"\"\"Deploy agent to Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n220:     try:\n221:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n222:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n223:         options = {\n224:             \"version\": version,\n225:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n226:             \"image_username\": image_username,\n227:             \"image_password\": image_password,\n228:             \"description\": description,\n229:             \"region\": region,\n230:             \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n231:             \"node_port\": node_port,\n232:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n233:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n234:         }\n235:         with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\")) as progress:\n236:             task = progress.add_task(\"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\", total=None)\n237:             result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n238:             progress.remove_task(task)\n239:         \n240:         console.print(f\"[green]Successfully published agent![/green]\")\n241:         console.print(f\"  Agent Name: {result['agent_name']}\")\n242:         console.print(f\"  Agent ID: {result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}\")\n243:         console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n244:         console.print(f\"  Deployment Type: {result['deployment_type']}\")\n245:         console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result['namespace']}\")\n246:         \n247:     except Exception as e:\n248:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### PublishRuntime Contract\n252: \n253: ```python\n254: class PublishRuntime:\n255:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n256:         self.verbose = verbose\n257:         self.provider = provider\n258:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n259:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n260:         \n261:         if provider == \"k8s\":\n262:             self.k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n263:         elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n264:             self.agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n265:         else:\n266:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n267: \n268:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n269:         \"\"\"\n270:         Orchestrates the publish workflow.\n271:         \n272:         Returns:\n273:             Dict containing agent_name, agent_id, agent_endpoint, deployment_type, namespace, k8s_deployment\n274:         \"\"\"\n275:         ...\n276: \n277:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n278:         \"\"\"Deploy via AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n279:         ...\n280: \n281:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n282:         \"\"\"Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n283:         ...\n284: \n285:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n286:         \"\"\"Return image URL ready for deployment.\"\"\"\n287:         ...\n288: \n289:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n290:         \"\"\"Push local Docker image to registry.\"\"\"\n291:         ...\n292: \n293:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n294:         \"\"\"Use cloud-built image URL.\"\"\"\n295:         ...\n296: \n297:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n298:         \"\"\"Persist deployment info to metadata YAML.\"\"\"\n299:         ...\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### AgentCubeProvider Contract\n303: \n304: ```python\n305: class AgentCubeProvider:\n306:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n307:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n308:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n309:     \n310:     def __init__(\n311:         self,\n312:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n313:         verbose: bool = False,\n314:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n315:     ) -> None:\n316:         self.namespace = namespace\n317:         self.verbose = verbose\n318:         \n319:         if kubeconfig:\n320:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n321:         else:\n322:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n323:         \n324:         self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()\n325:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n326: \n327:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n328:         self,\n329:         agent_name: str,\n330:         image_url: str,\n331:         port: int,\n332:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n333:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n334:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n335:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n336:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n337:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n338:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n339:         \"\"\"Create or patch AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n340:         ...\n341: \n342:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n343:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n344:         ...\n345: \n346:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n347:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n348:         ...\n349: \n350:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n351:         \"\"\"Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n352:         ...\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### KubernetesProvider Contract\n356: \n357: ```python\n358: class KubernetesProvider:\n359:     NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000\n360:     NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767\n361:     DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n362:     POLL_INTERVAL = 2\n363:     \n364:     def __init__(\n365:         self,\n366:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n367:         verbose: bool = False,\n368:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n369:     ) -> None:\n370:         self.namespace = namespace\n371:         self.verbose = verbose\n372:         \n373:         if kubeconfig:\n374:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n375:         else:\n376:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n377:         \n378:         self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()\n379:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n380: \n381:     def deploy_agent(\n382:         self,\n383:         agent_name: str,\n384:         image_url: str,\n385:         port: int,\n386:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n387:         replicas: int = 1,\n388:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n389:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n390:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n391:         \"\"\"Create Deployment + NodePort Service and wait for ready.\"\"\"\n392:         ...\n393: \n394:     def _create_deployment(\n395:         self,\n396:         name: str,\n397:         image_url: str,\n398:         port: int,\n399:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n400:         replicas: int,\n401:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n402:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n403:         \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n404:         ...\n405: \n406:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n407:         \"\"\"Create NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n408:         ...\n409: \n410:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n411:         \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n412:         ...\n413: \n414:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n415:         \"\"\"Get Deployment and Service status.\"\"\"\n416:         ...\n417: \n418:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n419:         \"\"\"Delete Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n420:         ...\n421: \n422:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n423:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n424:         ...\n425: \n426:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n427:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n428:         ...\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ---\n432: \n433: ## Error Handling\n434: \n435: ### Error Categories\n436: \n437: | Category | Exception Type | Message Pattern | Recovery |\n438: |----------|----------------|-----------------|----------|\n439: | Metadata Missing | `ValueError` | `Missing required field: {field} in agent_metadata.yaml` | User must add field |\n440: | Provider Invalid | `ValueError` | `Invalid provider: {value}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'` | Use valid provider |\n441: | Image URL Missing | `ValueError` | `--image-url is required for local build mode` | Provide image URL |\n442: | Router URL Missing | `ValueError` | `router_url is required for agentcube provider in agent_metadata.yaml` | Add router_url |\n443: | Workload Manager Missing | `ValueError` | `workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider` | Add workload_manager_url |\n444: | NodePort Invalid | `ValueError` | `NodePort must be in range 30000-32767` | Use valid NodePort |\n445: | Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | `Docker is not available or not running` | Start Docker |\n446: | Docker Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Failed to push image: {details}` | Check credentials |\n447: | K8s Unreachable | `RuntimeError` | `Kubernetes cluster is unreachable` | Check kubeconfig |\n448: | CRD Not Found | `ValueError` | `AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs` | Install CRDs |\n449: | Deployment Timeout | `TimeoutError` | `Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s` | Check pod logs |\n450: | Registry Auth Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Registry authentication failed: {details}` | Check credentials |\n451: \n452: ### Error Handling Pattern\n453: \n454: ```python\n455: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n456:     \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n457:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n458:     if verbose:\n459:         console.print_exception()\n460:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n461: ```\n462: \n463: ### Metadata Error Recording\n464: \n465: ```python\n466: def _record_error_in_metadata(workspace_path: Path, error_msg: str) -> None:\n467:     \"\"\"Record error in metadata before raising exception.\"\"\"\n468:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n469:     metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n470:         \"status\": \"error\",\n471:         \"error\": error_msg,\n472:     }\n473:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n474: ```\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## Testing Strategy\n479: \n480: ### Unit Tests\n481: \n482: | Test File | Coverage |\n483: |-----------|----------|\n484: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime orchestration, option overrides, provider selection |\n485: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | KubernetesProvider methods with mocked K8s API |\n486: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCubeProvider CR creation/patch with mocked API |\n487: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | push_image, login, tag methods |\n488: \n489: ### Mock Strategy\n490: \n491: ```python\n492: # Kubernetes API Mock\n493: @pytest.fixture\n494: def mock_k8s_api():\n495:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api\") as mock_apps:\n496:         with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\") as mock_core:\n497:             mock_apps.return_value.create_deployment.return_value = ...\n498:             mock_core.return_value.create_namespaced_service.return_value = ...\n499:             yield mock_apps, mock_core\n500: \n501: # AgentRuntime CR Mock\n502: @pytest.fixture\n503: def mock_custom_api():\n504:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\") as mock_custom:\n505:         mock_custom.return_value.create_custom_object.return_value = {\n506:             \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n507:             \"status\": {\"agentEndpoint\": \"http://test\"},\n508:         }\n509:         yield mock_custom\n510: \n511: # Docker Mock\n512: @pytest.fixture\n513: def mock_docker():\n514:     with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_client:\n515:         mock_client.return_value.images.push.return_value = [...]\n516:         yield mock_client\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ### Test Cases\n520: \n521: | Test Case | Scenario |\n522: |-----------|----------|\n523: | `test_publish_agentcube_success` | Valid metadata, agentcube provider, CR created |\n524: | `test_publish_k8s_success` | Valid metadata, k8s provider, Deployment + Service created |\n525: | `test_publish_missing_router_url` | agentcube provider without router_url raises ValueError |\n526: | `test_publish_missing_workload_manager` | agentcube provider without workload_manager_url raises ValueError |\n527: | `test_publish_invalid_provider` | Invalid provider raises ValueError |\n528: | `test_publish_image_url_required_local` | Local build mode without image_url raises ValueError |\n529: | `test_publish_node_port_out_of_range` | NodePort outside 30000-32767 raises ValueError |\n530: | `test_publish_deployment_timeout` | Deployment not ready after 120s raises TimeoutError |\n531: | `test_publish_metadata_update` | Metadata saved with agent_id and k8s_deployment |\n532: | `test_publish_error_metadata_update` | Error recorded in metadata before exception |\n533: | `test_k8s_provider_sanitize_name` | Name sanitized to DNS-compliant format |\n534: | `test_agentcube_provider_sanitize_name` | CR name sanitized |\n535: | `test_agentcube_provider_patch_existing_cr` | Patch instead of create for existing CR |\n536: | `test_docker_push_with_credentials` | Login + push with username/password |\n537: | `test_docker_push_without_credentials` | Push without login (pre-authenticated) |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## File Structure\n542: \n543: ```\n544: cmd/cli/\n545: ├── agentcube/\n546: │   ├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n547: │   ├── cli/\n548: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n549: │   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app + publish command\n550: │   ├── runtime/\n551: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n552: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # (AR-020)\n553: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # (AR-021)\n554: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # NEW: PublishRuntime\n555: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # (AR-023)\n556: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          # (AR-024)\n557: │   ├── services/\n558: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n559: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # Load/save metadata\n560: │   │   ├── docker_service.py          # EXTEND: push_image, login, tag\n561: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # NEW: KubernetesProvider\n562: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # NEW: AgentCubeProvider\n563: │   └── models/\n564: │       ├── __init__.py\n565: │       └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions\n566: ├── tests/\n567: │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py        # NEW\n568: │   ├── test_k8s_provider.py           # NEW\n569: │   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py     # NEW\n570: │   └── test_docker_service.py         # EXTEND\n571: ├── pyproject.toml                     # Dependencies\n572: └── examples/\n573:     └── hello-agent/\n574:         ├── main.py\n575:         └── agent_metadata.yaml        # Example metadata\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ---\n579: \n580: ## Dependencies\n581: \n582: ### Runtime Dependencies\n583: \n584: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n585: |---------|---------|---------|\n586: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n587: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n588: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n589: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n590: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client (optional `[k8s]` extras) |\n591: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n592: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n593: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n594: \n595: ### pyproject.toml Optional Dependencies\n596: \n597: ```toml\n598: [project.optional-dependencies]\n599: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n600: dev = [\n601:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n602:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n603:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n604:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n605:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n606:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n607:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n608: ]\n609: test = [\n610:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n611:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n612:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n613:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n614:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n615: ]\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ---\n619: \n620: ## Implementation Notes\n621: \n622: ### Constants\n623: \n624: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n625: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n626: | `CR_GROUP` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n627: | `CR_VERSION` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n628: | `CR_PLURAL` | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n629: | `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default session timeout |\n630: | `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default max session duration |\n631: | `DEFAULT_SECRET` | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default imagePullSecret |\n632: | `NODE_PORT_MIN` | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n633: | `NODE_PORT_MAX` | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n634: | `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Deployment readiness timeout |\n635: | `POLL_INTERVAL` | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Status poll interval (seconds) |\n636: \n637: ### AgentRuntime CR Template\n638: \n639: ```python\n640: cr_body = {\n641:     \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CR_GROUP}/{self.CR_VERSION}\",\n642:     \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n643:     \"metadata\": {\n644:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n645:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n646:     },\n647:     \"spec\": {\n648:         \"image\": image_url,\n649:         \"port\": port,\n650:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n651:         \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n652:         \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n653:         \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n654:         \"env\": [\n655:             {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n656:             {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n657:         ],\n658:         \"readinessProbe\": {\n659:             \"httpGet\": {\n660:                 \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n661:                 \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n662:             },\n663:         },\n664:     },\n665: }\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ### Kubernetes Deployment Template\n669: \n670: ```python\n671: deployment_body = {\n672:     \"apiVersion\": \"apps/v1\",\n673:     \"kind\": \"Deployment\",\n674:     \"metadata\": {\n675:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n676:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n677:         \"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n678:     },\n679:     \"spec\": {\n680:         \"replicas\": replicas,\n681:         \"selector\": {\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n682:         \"template\": {\n683:             \"metadata\": {\"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n684:             \"spec\": {\n685:                 \"containers\": [{\n686:                     \"name\": sanitized_name,\n687:                     \"image\": image_url,\n688:                     \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n689:                     \"env\": [{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()],\n690:                 }],\n691:             },\n692:         },\n693:     },\n694: }\n695: ```\n696: \n697: ### NodePort Service Template\n698: \n699: ```python\n700: service_body = {\n701:     \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n702:     \"kind\": \"Service\",\n703:     \"metadata\": {\n704:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n705:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n706:     },\n707:     \"spec\": {\n708:         \"type\": \"NodePort\",\n709:         \"selector\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n710:         \"ports\": [{\n711:             \"port\": port,\n712:             \"targetPort\": port,\n713:             \"nodePort\": node_port,  # Optional, K8s auto-assigns if None\n714:         }],\n715:     },\n716: }\n717: ```\n718: \n719: ### Name Sanitization Algorithm\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n723:     \"\"\"\n724:     Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\n725:     Rules:\n726:     - Lowercase only\n727:     - Replace non-alphanumeric with '-'\n728:     - Truncate to 63 characters\n729:     - Remove leading/trailing '-'\n730:     \"\"\"\n731:     sanitized = name.lower()\n732:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", sanitized)\n733:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"-+\", \"-\", sanitized)\n734:     sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n735:     return sanitized[:63]\n736: ```\n737: \n738: ### Wait for Deployment Ready Algorithm\n739: \n740: ```python\n741: def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n742:     start = time.time()\n743:     while time.time() - start < timeout:\n744:         deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n745:         if deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas:\n746:             return\n747:         time.sleep(self.POLL_INTERVAL)\n748:     raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s\")\n749: ```\n750: \n751: ---\n752: \n753: ## References\n754: \n755: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n756: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (publish command requirements)\n757: - deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n758: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n759: - AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n760: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n761: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n762: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n763: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n764: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n765: - Volcano AgentCube CRD: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n- **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n- **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775871569941,"end":1775871569962}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871569970,"sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31adb5001nweAcXuuNMr5ug","messageID":"msg_d7a318d630013FzasnKSQR70cO","sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3ca392ccab97454395578141d66c4f45","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: from pathlib import Path\n2: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n3: \n4: import yaml\n5: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n6: \n7: \n8: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n9:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n10:     description: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n11:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n12:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n13:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n14:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n15:     region: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Deployment region\")\n16:     version: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n17:     image: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description=\"Container image information\")\n18:     auth: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n19:     requirements_file: str = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n20:     registry_url: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n21:     registry_username: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n22:     registry_password: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n23:     agent_endpoint: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n24:     workload_manager_url: str = Field(\"\", description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n25:     router_url: str = Field(\"\", description=\"URL for the Router\")\n26:     readiness_probe_path: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n27:     readiness_probe_port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n28:     agent_id: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n29:     session_id: str = Field(\"\", description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n30:     k8s_deployment: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n31: \n32:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n33:     @classmethod\n34:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n35:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n36:         v_lower = v.lower()\n37:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n38:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n39:         return v_lower\n40: \n41:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n42:     @classmethod\n43:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n44:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n45:         v_lower = v.lower()\n46:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n47:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n48:         return v_lower\n49: \n50:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n51:     @classmethod\n52:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n53:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n54:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n55:         return v\n56: \n57: \n58: class MetadataService:\n59:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n60:         self.verbose = verbose\n61: \n62:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n63:         metadata_files = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n64:         for filename in metadata_files:\n65:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n66:             if filepath.exists():\n67:                 with open(filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n68:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n69:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n70:         raise FileNotFoundError(\n71:             f\"No metadata file found in workspace: {workspace_path}\"\n72:         )\n73: \n74:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Path:\n75:         filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n76:         data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n77:         with open(filepath, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n78:             yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n79:         return filepath\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"from pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\nimport yaml\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    region: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    image: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    requirements_file: str = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    registry_url: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py","time":{"start":1775871569944,"end":1775871569968}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871569973,"sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31afc9001d9BFQ8c6YDNGe8","messageID":"msg_d7a318d630013FzasnKSQR70cO","sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-807f124a06d84ac5a6912dd7e6567641","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import logging\n2: import re\n3: from pathlib import Path\n4: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n5: \n6: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n7: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n8: \n9: \n10: DEFAULT_TAG = \"latest\"\n11: \n12: \n13: class BuildRuntime:\n14:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n15:         self.verbose = verbose\n16:         self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n17:         self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n18:         self._logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n19: \n20:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n21:         metadata = self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n22:         original_version = metadata.version\n23:         self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n24:         \n25:         try:\n26:             new_tag = self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n27:             \n28:             if metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\":\n29:                 build_result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options, new_tag)\n30:             else:\n31:                 build_result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options, new_tag)\n32:             \n33:             self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, new_tag)\n34:             \n35:             return {\n36:                 \"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"],\n37:                 \"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"],\n38:                 \"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"],\n39:                 \"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"],\n40:                 \"tag\": new_tag,\n41:                 \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n42:                 \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n43:                 \"status\": \"success\",\n44:             }\n45:         except Exception as e:\n46:             metadata.version = original_version\n47:             self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n48:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")\n49: \n50:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n51:         if not self._docker_service.check_docker_available():\n52:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n53:         \n54:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n55:         if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n56:             raise ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace. Please run 'pack' command first.\")\n57: \n58:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n59:         current_version = metadata.version\n60:         \n61:         if not current_version or current_version.strip() == \"\":\n62:             metadata.version = DEFAULT_TAG\n63:             self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n64:             return DEFAULT_TAG\n65:         \n66:         stripped_version = current_version.strip()\n67:         has_v_prefix = stripped_version.startswith(\"v\")\n68:         version_core = stripped_version[1:] if has_v_prefix else stripped_version\n69:         \n70:         semver_pattern = re.compile(r\"^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$\")\n71:         if semver_pattern.match(version_core):\n72:             parts = version_core.split(\".\")\n73:             parts[2] = str(int(parts[2]) + 1)\n74:             new_version = \".\".join(parts)\n75:             new_tag = f\"v{new_version}\" if has_v_prefix else new_version\n76:         elif re.match(r\"^\\d+\\.\\d+$\", version_core):\n77:             new_tag = f\"{stripped_version}.1\"\n78:         else:\n79:             new_tag = f\"{stripped_version}-1\"\n80:         \n81:         metadata.version = new_tag\n82:         self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n83:         return new_tag\n84: \n85:     def _build_local(\n86:         self, \n87:         workspace_path: Path, \n88:         metadata: AgentMetadata, \n89:         options: Dict[str, Any], \n90:         tag: str\n91:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n92:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n93:         \n94:         build_args: Dict[str, str] = {}\n95:         proxy = options.get(\"proxy\")\n96:         if proxy:\n97:             build_args[\"HTTP_PROXY\"] = proxy\n98:             build_args[\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] = proxy\n99:         \n100:         return self._docker_service.build_image(\n101:             dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n102:             context_path=workspace_path,\n103:             image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n104:             tag=tag,\n105:             build_args=build_args,\n106:             verbose=self.verbose,\n107:         )\n108: \n109:     def _build_cloud(\n110:         self, \n111:         workspace_path: Path, \n112:         metadata: AgentMetadata, \n113:         options: Dict[str, Any], \n114:         tag: str\n115:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n116:         self._logger.warning(\"Cloud build not implemented\")\n117:         return {\n118:             \"image_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n119:             \"image_id\": \"cloud-placeholder\",\n120:             \"image_size\": \"0 MB\",\n121:             \"build_time\": 0,\n122:             \"tag\": tag,\n123:         }\n124: \n125:     def _update_build_metadata(\n126:         self, \n127:         workspace_path: Path, \n128:         metadata: AgentMetadata, \n129:         build_result: Dict[str, Any], \n130:         tag: str\n131:     ) -> None:\n132:         metadata.image = {\n133:             \"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"],\n134:             \"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"],\n135:             \"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"],\n136:             \"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"],\n137:             \"tag\": tag,\n138:         }\n139:         self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n(End of file - total 139 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import logging\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\nfrom agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n\n\nDEFAULT_TAG = \"latest\"\n\n\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n        self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n        self._logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py","time":{"start":1775871569947,"end":1775871569970}}}}
