{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871585300,"sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31ebe9001PoFLBttXmCQv6T","messageID":"msg_d7a31d2010011lFBQ6OCcuwOBy","sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7a74883dbab8465194d231b2df38e42a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Add `get_image_info()` method to `DockerService`\n20:   - Extract image_id, image_size, and format size to human-readable string\n21:   - Signature: `get_image_info(image_name: str, tag: str) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n22:   - Return: `{\"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str}`\n23:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n24:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_image_info -v`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T1.2**: Add `_format_size()` helper method to `DockerService`\n27:   - Convert bytes to human-readable format (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n28:   - Handle KB, MB, GB ranges\n29:   - Private method used by `get_image_info()`\n30:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n31:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_format_size -v`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.3**: Update `build_image()` method signature and return structure\n34:   - Add `dockerfile_path` parameter (separate from context_path)\n35:   - Add `build_args` parameter for proxy support\n36:   - Return `{\"image_name\": str, \"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str, \"build_time\": float, \"tag\": str}`\n37:   - Stream build logs when `verbose=True`\n38:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n39:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_build_image_with_proxy -v`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T1.4**: Add `check_docker_available()` method improvements\n42:   - Return `True/False` boolean (already exists, verify correctness)\n43:   - Log Docker daemon status in verbose mode\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n45:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_check_docker_available -v`\n46: \n47: ### Phase 2: BuildRuntime Class (ST-2)\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `BuildRuntime` class skeleton in `build_runtime.py`\n50:   - Import dependencies: `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n51:   - Import services: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`\n52:   - Define constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n53:   - Initialize `self.verbose`, `self._metadata_service`, `self._docker_service`\n54:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n55:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\"`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `build()` main entry method\n58:   - Signature: `build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n59:   - Load metadata via `self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n60:   - Store `original_version = metadata.version` for rollback\n61:   - Call `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)`\n62:   - Call `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` → returns `new_tag`\n63:   - Call `_build_local()` or `_build_cloud()` based on `metadata.build_mode`\n64:   - Call `_update_build_metadata()` on success\n65:   - Rollback version on failure, raise `RuntimeError`\n66:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n67:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_validate_build_prerequisites()` method\n70:   - Check `self._docker_service.check_docker_available()` → raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available\")`\n71:   - Check `workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"` exists → raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found\")`\n72:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n73:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_docker_unavailable -v`\n74: \n75: ### Phase 3: Version Increment Logic (ST-3)\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `_increment_version()` method\n78:   - Import `semver` library\n79:   - Handle valid semver `X.Y.Z` → bump_patch → `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n80:   - Handle `v`-prefixed non-semver `vX.Y` → append `.1` → `vX.Y.1`\n81:   - Handle non-semver string → append `-1` → `custom-1`\n82:   - Handle `None/empty` → return `\"latest\"`\n83:   - Save updated `metadata.version` via `self._metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n84:   - Return new tag string\n85:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_increment_semver -v`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Add version rollback logic in `build()` method\n89:   - Store `original_version` before increment\n90:   - On exception in build: `metadata.version = original_version`\n91:   - Call `self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n92:   - Raise `RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")`\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_rollback_on_failure -v`\n95: \n96: ### Phase 4: Build Execution Methods (ST-4)\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `_build_local()` method\n99:   - Resolve image_name: `metadata.agent_name`\n100:   - Build args: `{\"PROXY\": options.get(\"proxy\")}` if proxy provided\n101:   - Call `self._docker_service.build_image()` with:\n102:     - `dockerfile_path=workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"`\n103:     - `context_path=workspace_path`\n104:     - `image_name=metadata.agent_name`\n105:     - `tag=new_tag`\n106:     - `build_args=build_args`\n107:   - Return build result dict\n108:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `_build_cloud()` placeholder method\n112:   - Check `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n113:   - Return placeholder dict: `{\"image_name\": metadata.agent_name, \"image_id\": \"cloud-placeholder\", \"image_size\": \"0 MB\", \"build_time\": 0, \"tag\": \"latest\"}`\n114:   - Log warning: `\"Cloud build not implemented\"`\n115:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n116:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_cloud_placeholder -v`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `_update_build_metadata()` method\n119:   - Update `metadata.image` dict with:\n120:     - `\"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"]`\n121:     - `\"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"]`\n122:     - `\"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"]`\n123:     - `\"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"]`\n124:     - `\"tag\": tag`\n125:   - Call `self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n126:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n127:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_update_build_metadata -v`\n128: \n129: ### Phase 5: CLI Command Implementation (ST-5)\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.1**: Add `build` command to `main.py`\n132:   - Import `BuildRuntime` from `agentcube.runtime.build_runtime`\n133:   - Define Typer command with options:\n134:     - `workspace: str = \".\"` (alias `-f`, `--workspace`)\n135:     - `proxy: Optional[str] = None` (alias `-p`, `--proxy`)\n136:     - `cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None` (`--cloud-provider`)\n137:     - `output: Optional[str] = None` (`--output`)\n138:     - `verbose: bool = False` (`--verbose`)\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n140:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube build --help`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `build` command handler\n143:   - Resolve workspace path: `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n144:   - Initialize `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)`\n145:   - Use Rich Progress spinner: `progress.add_task(\"Building agent image...\", total=None)`\n146:   - Call `runtime.build(workspace_path, proxy=proxy, cloud_provider=cloud_provider, output=output)`\n147:   - Print success output with Rich formatting:\n148:     - `[green]Build completed successfully[/green]`\n149:     - `Image: {image_name}:{tag}`\n150:     - `Image ID: {image_id}`\n151:     - `Size: {image_size}`\n152:     - `Build time: {build_time}s`\n153:   - Handle errors via `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)`\n154:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n155:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py -v` (update test)\n156: \n157: ### Phase 6: Unit Tests - BuildRuntime (ST-6)\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create test file `test_build_runtime.py`\n160:   - Import `pytest`, `unittest.mock`, `Path`\n161:   - Import `BuildRuntime`, `AgentMetadata`\n162:   - Create fixtures: `mock_docker_service`, `mock_metadata_service`, `tmp_workspace`\n163:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n164:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T6.2**: Test `build_local_success`\n167:   - Mock DockerService to return valid build result\n168:   - Mock MetadataService to load/save metadata\n169:   - Verify build returns correct result dict\n170:   - Verify metadata.version incremented\n171:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n172:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T6.3**: Test `build_docker_unavailable`\n175:   - Mock `check_docker_available()` to return `False`\n176:   - Expect `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n177:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n178:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_docker_unavailable -v`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T6.4**: Test `build_missing_dockerfile`\n181:   - Create tmp workspace without Dockerfile\n182:   - Expect `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n183:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n184:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_missing_dockerfile -v`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T6.5**: Test version increment scenarios\n187:   - Test semver: `1.2.3` → `1.2.4`\n188:   - Test v-prefix semver: `v1.2.3` → `v1.2.4`\n189:   - Test v-prefix non-semver: `v1.0` → `v1.0.1`\n190:   - Test non-semver: `custom` → `custom-1`\n191:   - Test empty: `None` → `\"latest\"`\n192:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n193:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_increment -v`\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T6.6**: Test version rollback on failure\n196:   - Mock `build_image()` to raise `BuildError`\n197:   - Verify metadata.version restored to original\n198:   - Verify `RuntimeError` raised with rollback message\n199:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n200:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_rollback_on_failure -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T6.7**: Test `build_cloud_placeholder`\n203:   - Set `metadata.build_mode = \"cloud\"`\n204:   - Verify placeholder dict returned\n205:   - Verify warning logged\n206:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n207:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_cloud_placeholder -v`\n208: \n209: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests - DockerService (ST-7)\n210: \n211: - [ ] **T7.1**: Create/update `test_docker_service.py`\n212:   - Test `check_docker_available()` with mocked Docker client\n213:   - Test `build_image()` with mocked `client.images.build()`\n214:   - Test `get_image_info()` with mocked image object\n215:   - Test `_format_size()` helper method\n216:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n217:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v`\n218: \n219: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test `build_image_with_proxy`\n220:   - Mock Docker build API\n221:   - Pass `build_args={\"PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}`\n222:   - Verify buildargs passed to Docker API\n223:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n224:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_build_image_with_proxy -v`\n225: \n226: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test `get_image_info`\n227:   - Mock image with `id=\"sha256:abc123\"` and `attrs[\"Size\"]=125300000`\n228:   - Verify returns `{\"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123\", \"image_size\": \"125.3 MB\"}`\n229:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n230:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_image_info -v`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test `_format_size` helper\n233:   - Test bytes: `500` → `\"500 B\"`\n234:   - Test KB: `1024` → `\"1.0 KB\"`\n235:   - Test MB: `1048576` → `\"1.0 MB\"`\n236:   - Test GB: `1073741824` → `\"1.0 GB\"`\n237:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n238:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_format_size -v`\n239: \n240: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests (ST-8)\n241: \n242: - [ ] **T8.1**: Create integration test `test_build_integration.py`\n243:   - Test full workflow: validate → increment → build → update metadata\n244:   - Use tmp workspace with Dockerfile and agent_metadata.yaml\n245:   - Mock Docker SDK for build execution\n246:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n247:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py -v`\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T8.2**: Test `build_after_pack` integration\n250:   - Pack creates Dockerfile, build succeeds\n251:   - Verify metadata.image updated correctly\n252:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n253:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py::TestBuildIntegration::test_build_after_pack -v`\n254: \n255: - [ ] **T8.3**: Test `rebuild_increments_version` integration\n256:   - First build: `version=\"v1.0\"` → `tag=\"v1.0.1\"`\n257:   - Second build: `version=\"v1.0.1\"` → `tag=\"v1.0.2\"`\n258:   - Verify version increments on each build\n259:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n260:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py::TestBuildIntegration::test_rebuild_increments_version -v`\n261: \n262: ### Phase 9: Dependencies & Validation (ST-9)\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T9.1**: Add `semver` dependency to `pyproject.toml`\n265:   - Version: `semver>=3.0.0`\n266:   - Purpose: Semantic version parsing and bumping\n267:   - File: `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n268:   - Verification: `pip install semver && python -c \"import semver\"`\n269: \n270: - [ ] **T9.2**: Update `runtime/__init__.py` exports\n271:   - Add `BuildRuntime` to exports\n272:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n273:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import BuildRuntime\"`\n274: \n275: - [ ] **T9.3**: Run all tests with coverage\n276:   - `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing`\n277:   - Coverage target: >80% for `build_runtime.py`\n278:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/`\n279:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube`\n280: \n281: - [ ] **T9.4**: Run lint and type check\n282:   - `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n283:   - `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n284:   - Fix any lint/type errors\n285:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n286:   - Verification: `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/ && mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ## Task Dependencies\n291: \n292: ```\n293: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3 → T1.4\n294:            ↓\n295:         T2.1 → T2.2 → T2.3\n296:                ↓\n297:         T3.1 → T3.2\n298:                ↓\n299:         T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3\n300:                ↓\n301:         T5.1 → T5.2\n302:                ↓\n303:         T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4 → T6.5 → T6.6 → T6.7\n304:                ↓\n305:         T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4\n306:                ↓\n307:         T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3\n308:                ↓\n309:         T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3 → T9.4\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Verification Commands\n315: \n316: | Task | Verification Command |\n317: |------|----------------------|\n318: | DockerService tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n319: | BuildRuntime tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v` |\n320: | Integration tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py -v` |\n321: | All tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v` |\n322: | Coverage | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` |\n323: | Build command help | `kubectl-agentcube build --help` |\n324: | Lint check | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n325: | Type check | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n326: | Import test | `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\"` |\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Acceptance Criteria\n331: \n332: - [ ] `BuildRuntime` class defined with `__init__`, `build`, `_validate_build_prerequisites`\n333: - [ ] `_increment_version()` handles semver, v-prefix, non-semver, None cases\n334: - [ ] `_build_local()` calls DockerService with correct parameters\n335: - [ ] `_build_cloud()` returns placeholder for cloud mode\n336: - [ ] `_update_build_metadata()` updates `metadata.image` dict\n337: - [ ] Version rollback on build failure\n338: - [ ] `build` Typer command with all options: `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n339: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner during build\n340: - [ ] Success output: image name, ID, size, build time\n341: - [ ] Error handling via `_handle_error()`\n342: - [ ] DockerService `get_image_info()` method\n343: - [ ] DockerService `_format_size()` helper\n344: - [ ] DockerService `build_image()` with `build_args` support\n345: - [ ] Unit tests for version increment scenarios\n346: - [ ] Unit tests for rollback logic\n347: - [ ] Unit tests for Docker unavailable/missing Dockerfile\n348: - [ ] Integration tests for build workflow\n349: - [ ] Integration test for pack→build workflow\n350: - [ ] Integration test for rebuild version increment\n351: - [ ] `semver>=3.0.0` dependency added\n352: - [ ] `BuildRuntime` exported from `runtime/__init__.py`\n353: - [ ] All tests pass with >80% coverage\n354: - [ ] Ruff lint passes\n355: - [ ] MyPy type check passes\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## File Changes Summary\n360: \n361: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n362: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n363: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Create | ~120 | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration |\n364: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modify | ~5 | Export `BuildRuntime` |\n365: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | ~30 | Add `get_image_info`, `_format_size`, update `build_image` |\n366: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modify | ~40 | Add `build` command with Typer options |\n367: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Create | ~200 | Unit tests for BuildRuntime |\n368: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` | Modify | ~50 | Unit tests for new DockerService methods |\n369: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py` | Create | ~80 | Integration tests for build workflow |\n370: | `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` | Modify | ~2 | Add `semver>=3.0.0` dependency |\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ## Implementation Notes\n375: \n376: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n377: - **Reference implementation**: `PackRuntime` in `pack_runtime.py` provides similar pattern\n378: - **DockerService already exists** with `check_docker_available` and `build_image` - enhance these\n379: - **semver library**: Use `semver.VersionInfo.parse()` and `bump_patch()` for version increment\n380: - **Version increment strategy**:\n381:   - Valid semver `X.Y.Z`: bump_patch → `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n382:   - v-prefixed semver `vX.Y.Z`: preserve prefix → `vX.Y.(Z+1)`\n383:   - v-prefixed non-semver `vX.Y`: append `.1` → `vX.Y.1`\n384:   - Non-semver string: append `-1` → `string-1`\n385:   - None/empty: use `\"latest\"`\n386: - **Proxy support**: Pass as `build_args={\"PROXY\": proxy_url}` to Docker SDK\n387: - **Rollback pattern**: Store original version, restore on exception\n388: - **Rich Progress**: Use `SpinnerColumn` + `TextColumn` for build spinner\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Implementation Timeline\n393: \n394: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n395: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n396: | Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3, T1.4 | Pending | 0% |\n397: | Phase 2: BuildRuntime Class | T2.1, T2.2, T2.3 | Pending | 0% |\n398: | Phase 3: Version Increment Logic | T3.1, T3.2 | Pending | 0% |\n399: | Phase 4: Build Execution Methods | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3 | Pending | 0% |\n400: | Phase 5: CLI Command Implementation | T5.1, T5.2 | Pending | 0% |\n401: | Phase 6: Unit Tests - BuildRuntime | T6.1-T6.7 | Pending | 0% |\n402: | Phase 7: Unit Tests - DockerService | T7.1-T7.4 | Pending | 0% |\n403: | Phase 8: Integration Tests | T8.1-T8.3 | Pending | 0% |\n404: | Phase 9: Dependencies & Validation | T9.1-T9.4 | Pending | 0% |\n405: \n406: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/29 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 406 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Add `get_image_info()` method to `DockerService`\n  - Extract image_id, image_size, and format size to human-readable string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775871585286,"end":1775871585297}}}}
