{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871808175,"sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3551e1001eos6sP7WZPr0Sw","messageID":"msg_d7a31ec48001m6g37Nw408U92n","sessionID":"ses_285cec074ffeL3mWKyuYgUnYwe","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-c9c1ff6e82df4e7fa701a61a9a10f076","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/tasks.md","content":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Metadata Model Extensions (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Add `k8s_deployment` field to `AgentMetadata`\n  - Type: `Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)`\n  - Purpose: Store Kubernetes deployment information\n  - Fields: `type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`, `status`, `error`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_k8s_deployment_field -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Add `agent_id` field to `AgentMetadata`\n  - Type: `str = Field(\"\", description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")`\n  - Purpose: Unique identifier assigned by AgentCube provider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_id_field -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3**: Add `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` fields\n  - `readiness_probe_path: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Path for readiness probe\")`\n  - `readiness_probe_port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")`\n  - Purpose: Configure health check endpoints for AgentRuntime CR\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_readiness_probe_fields -v`\n\n### Phase 2: KubernetesProvider Class (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Create `k8s_provider.py` skeleton\n  - Import: `kubernetes`, `time`, `re`, `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n  - Define constants: `NODE_PORT_MIN=30000`, `NODE_PORT_MAX=32767`, `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120`, `POLL_INTERVAL=2`\n  - Define class: `class KubernetesProvider`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n  - Load kubeconfig: `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` or default\n  - Initialize APIs: `self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_init -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method\n  - Convert name to lowercase DNS-compliant (max 63 chars)\n  - Pattern: `re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", name.lower())`\n  - Truncate to 63 chars, remove leading/trailing `-`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n  - Check if namespace exists via `self.core_api.read_namespace()`\n  - Create if not exists: `self.core_api.create_namespace()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.5**: Implement `_create_deployment()` method\n  - Build Deployment body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n  - Include: `replicas`, `selector`, `template` with container spec\n  - Container: `name`, `image`, `ports`, `env` from env_vars\n  - Call `self.apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_deployment -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `_create_service()` method\n  - Build NodePort Service body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n  - Type: `NodePort`, selector matching deployment labels\n  - Port mapping: `port`, `targetPort`, optional `nodePort`\n  - Call `self.core_api.create_namespaced_service()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_service -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n  - Poll `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()` status\n  - Check `deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas`\n  - Sleep `POLL_INTERVAL` seconds between checks\n  - Raise `TimeoutError` if `timeout` exceeded\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_wait_for_ready -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `deploy_agent()` main method\n  - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n  - Validate `node_port` in range 30000-32767 if provided\n  - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n  - Call `_create_deployment()`, `_create_service()`\n  - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n  - Return deployment info dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_deploy_agent -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.9**: Implement `get_agent_status()` method\n  - Read Deployment: `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()`\n  - Read Service: `self.core_api.read_namespaced_service()`\n  - Return combined status dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_get_status -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.10**: Implement `delete_agent()` method\n  - Delete Deployment: `self.apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment()`\n  - Delete Service: `self.core_api.delete_namespaced_service()`\n  - Return deletion status dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_delete_agent -v`\n\n### Phase 3: AgentCubeProvider Class (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Create `agentcube_provider.py` skeleton\n  - Import: `kubernetes`, `re`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n  - Define constants: `CR_GROUP=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `CR_VERSION=\"v1alpha1\"`, `CR_PLURAL=\"agentruntimes\"`\n  - Define class: `class AgentCubeProvider`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\"`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n  - Load kubeconfig\n  - Initialize APIs: `self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_init -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method (reuse pattern from KubernetesProvider)\n  - Same DNS-compliant sanitization logic\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n  - Same pattern as KubernetesProvider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `deploy_agent_runtime()` method\n  - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n  - Validate required fields: `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n  - Build AgentRuntime CR body with spec\n  - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n  - Try `create_namespaced_custom_object()`, catch 409 → `patch_namespaced_custom_object()`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_deploy_agent_runtime -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.6**: Implement AgentRuntime CR body template\n  - `apiVersion`: `\"{CR_GROUP}/{CR_VERSION}\"`\n  - `kind`: `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - `spec`: `image`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `sessionTimeout=\"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"`\n  - `spec.env`: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL\n  - `spec.readinessProbe`: httpGet with path and port\n  - `spec.imagePullSecrets`: default-secret\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_cr_template -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.7**: Implement `get_agent_runtime()` method\n  - Call `self.custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object()`\n  - Return CR status dict or `None` if not found\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_get_agent_runtime -v`\n\n### Phase 4: DockerService Enhancements (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Enhance `push_image()` method\n  - Already exists, verify handles registry_url, username, password\n  - Add proper error handling for push failures\n  - Return `{\"pushed_image\": str, \"push_time\": float}`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_push_image -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Add `tag_image()` method\n  - Parameters: `source_image: str`, `target_image: str`\n  - Call `client.images.get(source_image).tag(target_image)`\n  - Return `{\"tagged_image\": str}`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_tag_image -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Add `login()` method\n  - Parameters: `registry_url: str`, `username: str`, `password: str`\n  - Call `client.login(username, password, registry=registry_url)`\n  - Handle authentication failure with proper error message\n  - Return `{\"registry\": str, \"status\": str}`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_login -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Add `get_local_image_url()` method\n  - Parameters: `image_name: str`, `tag: str`\n  - Check if image exists locally\n  - Return full image name with tag\n  - Raise error if image not found\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_local_image_url -v`\n\n### Phase 5: PublishRuntime Class (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Create `publish_runtime.py` skeleton\n  - Import: `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`, `logging`\n  - Import services: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`, `KubernetesProvider`, `AgentCubeProvider`\n  - Define class: `class PublishRuntime`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\"`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `PublishRuntime.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `verbose: bool = False`, `provider: str = \"agentcube\"`\n  - Initialize `self.verbose`, `self.metadata_service`, `self.docker_service`\n  - Validate provider: must be `\"agentcube\"` or `\"k8s\"`\n  - Initialize appropriate provider: `AgentCubeProvider` or `KubernetesProvider`\n  - Raise `ValueError` for invalid provider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_init -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `publish()` main entry method\n  - Signature: `publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n  - Load metadata via `self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n  - Apply CLI option overrides to metadata\n  - Call `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`\n  - Route to `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` or `_publish_k8s()` based on provider\n  - Call `_update_publish_metadata()` on success\n  - Return result dict with: `agent_name`, `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `deployment_type`, `namespace`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_publish_success -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` method\n  - Check `metadata.build_mode`\n  - Call `_prepare_local_image()` for `local` mode\n  - Call `_prepare_cloud_image()` for `cloud` mode\n  - Return image URL string ready for deployment\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::TestPublishRuntime::test_prepare_image -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `_prepare_local_image()` method\n  - Validate `image_url` provided via CLI or metadata\n  - Get local image via `docker_service.get_local_image_url()`\n  - Tag image if registry_url differs: `docker_service.tag_image()`\n  - Login to registry if credentials provided: `docker_service.login()`\n  - Push image: `docker_service.push_image()`\